  "text": "In a prospective study of almost 30 000 individuals followed for 9 years, a low thyrotropin (TSH) level, suggestive of subclinical hyperthyroidism (TSH <0.5 mU/l), was associated with increased cancer risk specifically with lung (hazard ratio 2.60) and prostate cancers (hazard ratio 1.96). Hypothyroid function was not associated with cancer risk [CITATION_1] .",
